	<entry>
		<title>VulkanSceneGraph Project</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.openscenegraph.com/index.php/8-news/232-vulkan-vkscenegraph-project"/>
		<published>2018-11-24T09:48:36+00:00</published>
		<updated>2018-11-24T09:48:36+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://www.openscenegraph.com/index.php/8-news/232-vulkan-vkscenegraph-project</id>
		<author>
			<name>Super User</name>
			<email>robert@openscenegraph.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.openscenegraph.com/images/vsg-small.png&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; alt=&quot;vsg-logo&quot; style=&quot;border: 0;&quot; /&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vulkanscenegraph.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Vulkan/VkSceneGraph&quot;&gt;VulkanSceneGraph &lt;/a&gt;project is now underway,&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vulkanscenegraph.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Vulkan/VkSceneGraph&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt;combining Vulkan and C++17 to create a next-gen scene graph.  Developed under the auspices of OpenSceneGraph Project Lead, the new project is the natural successor to the OpenSceneGraph, with the OpenSceneGraph project remaining supported and moved to a maintenance phase.  The new project is hosted on&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/vsg-dev&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;vsg project page&quot;&gt; github&lt;/a&gt; and will be developed over the coming year with the goal of a stable 1.0 release late 2019.  For support head over to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/vsg-users&quot;&gt;vsg-users&lt;/a&gt; googlegroup.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.openscenegraph.com/images/vsg-small.png&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; alt=&quot;vsg-logo&quot; style=&quot;border: 0;&quot; /&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vulkanscenegraph.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Vulkan/VkSceneGraph&quot;&gt;VulkanSceneGraph &lt;/a&gt;project is now underway,&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vulkanscenegraph.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Vulkan/VkSceneGraph&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt;combining Vulkan and C++17 to create a next-gen scene graph.  Developed under the auspices of OpenSceneGraph Project Lead, the new project is the natural successor to the OpenSceneGraph, with the OpenSceneGraph project remaining supported and moved to a maintenance phase.  The new project is hosted on&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/vsg-dev&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;vsg project page&quot;&gt; github&lt;/a&gt; and will be developed over the coming year with the goal of a stable 1.0 release late 2019.  For support head over to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/vsg-users&quot;&gt;vsg-users&lt;/a&gt; googlegroup.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
		<category term="Featured" />
		<category term="News" />
	</entry>
